explanation: The algorithm iteratively compares the last characters of the three strings. If they are not equal, it deletes the last character of the mismatching strings. It continues this process until all strings have the same last character or one of the strings becomes empty. The time complexity is linear as it iterates through the strings at most n times, where n is the length of the longest string. The space complexity is constant as it only uses a few variables. The energy implications are low as it performs constant-time operations.

